 find an excess of 850 micron emission relative to what\nwould be predicted by dust models. The 850 micron excess is highest in regions\nwith low 160 micron surface brightness, although the strength and statistical\nsignificance of this result depends on the model fit to the data. We rule out\nvariable emissivity functions or ~4 K dust as the possible origins of this 850\nmicron emission, but we do discuss the other possible mechanisms that could\nproduce the emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Jul 2006 09:12:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-08-27"}
